00:21:56,621 --> 00:21:59,057
So serious.

243
00:22:39,731 --> 00:22:44,169
I believeyou are blushing,
Mr. Big Artiste.

244
00:22:47,539 --> 00:22:51,109
I can't imagine
Monsieur Monet blushing.

245
00:22:51,176 --> 00:22:55,513
He does landscapes.
Just relaxyourface.

246
00:22:55,580 --> 00:22:58,183
- Sorry.
- No laughing.

247
00:22:58,249 --> 00:23:00,618
( Exhales)

248
00:23:29,147 --> 00:23:32,517
My heart was pounding
the whole time.

249
00:23:32,584 --> 00:23:36,554
It was the most erotic moment
of my life.

250
00:23:40,091 --> 00:23:42,861
Up until then, at least.

251
00:23:42,927 --> 00:23:48,533
- So what happened next?
- You mean, did we do it?

252
00:23:50,735 --> 00:23:53,171
Sorry, to disappointyou,
Mr. Bodine.

253
00:23:53,238 --> 00:23:56,074
Jackwas very professional.

254
00:24:04,115 --> 00:24:06,484
Thankyou.

255
00:24:07,552 --> 00:24:09,654
( RoseLaughing)

256
00:24:13,057 --> 00:24:14,993
Whatyou doing?

257
00:24:15,059 --> 00:24:17,395
Will you put this back
in the safe for me?

258
00:24:17,462 --> 00:24:19,397
Mm-hmm.

259
00:24:29,908 --> 00:24:32,310
Would you excuse me?

260
00:24:34,245 --> 00:24:38,917
- None ofthe stewards have seen her.
- This is absurd.

261
00:24:38,983 --> 00:24:42,287
It's a ship, there's only
so many places she could be.

262
00:24:42,353 --> 00:24:44,289
Lovejoy, find her.

263
00:25:01,472 --> 00:25:04,309
- Clear.
- Yes.

264
00:25:04,375 --> 00:25:08,580
I don't think I've ever seen
such a flat calm.

265
00:25:08,646 --> 00:25:13,251
Like a mill pond.
Not a breath ofwind.

266
00:25:13,318 --> 00:25:16,754
It will make the bergs
harderto see

267
00:25:16,821 --> 00:25:20,692
with no breaking water
at the base.

268
00:25:20,758 --> 00:25:22,694
Hmm.

269
00:25:30,201 --> 00:25:34,539
Well, I'm off. Maintain speed
and heading, Mr. Lightoller.

270
00:25:34,606 --> 00:25:36,541
Yes, sir.

271
00:25:47,685 --> 00:25:49,754
It's getting cold.
You look nice.

272
00:25:49,821 --> 00:25:52,090
- ( KnockAtDoor)
- Lovejoy: Miss Rose?

273
00:25:52,156 --> 00:25:54,092
My drawings!

274
00:26:00,532 --> 00:26:02,767
( DoorCloses)

275
00:26:20,151 --> 00:26:22,220
Come on!

276
00:26:24,355 --> 00:26:27,926
- No, wait, wait!
- Wait, wait, wait!

277
00:26:27,992 --> 00:26:30,195
Go, go! Down, down!

278
00:26:30,261 --> 00:26:33,431
Rose:
Quickly, quickly!

279
00:26:36,067 --> 00:26:38,303
( Giggling)
Bye!

280
00:26:45,777 --> 00:26:48,279
- Sorry!
- ( Giggling)

281
00:26:52,851 --> 00:26:56,521
- It's all right!
- ( Laughing)

282
00:27:04,596 --> 00:27:07,131
Prettytough for a valet,
this fellow.

283
00:27:07,198 --> 00:27:09,934
- Seems more like a cop.
- I think he was.

284
00:27:10,001 --> 00:27:12,337
-Jack: Oh, shit.
- ( RoseScreams)

285
00:27:17,141 --> 00:27:19,077
No, over here!

286
00:27:19,143 --> 00:27:21,079
Quick!

287
00:27:23,548 --> 00:27:26,718
( BoilerBlasting)

288
00:27:26,784 --> 00:27:30,021
- Now what?!
- What?!

289
00:27:37,028 --> 00:27:39,664
Hold up! What'reyou two
doing down here?

290
00:27:39,731 --> 00:27:43,501
You shouldn't be down here!
It could be dangerous!

291
00:27:46,204 --> 00:27:49,974
Jack: Carry on! Don't mind us.
You're doing a greatjob!

292
00:27:50,041 --> 00:27:51,976
Keep up the good work!

293
00:28:07,859 --> 00:28:10,562
Ah, lookwhat
we have here, huh?

294
00:28:21,206 --> 00:28:23,474
( Rose Clears Throat)

295
00:28:28,413 --> 00:28:30,348
Thankyou.

296
00:28:39,991 --> 00:28:44,095
- ( Honks Horn )
- Where to, miss?

297
00:28:44,162 --> 00:28:46,364
To the stars.

298
00:29:05,183 --> 00:29:07,151
You nervous?

299
00:29:09,254 --> 00:29:11,589
No.

300
00:29:26,938 --> 00:29:29,774
Putyour hands on me,Jack.

301
00:29:52,564 --> 00:29:54,699
Crewman:
God, it's bloody cold.

302
00:29:54,766 --> 00:30:00,004
You know, I can smell ice,
you know, when it's near.

303
00:30:00,071 --> 00:30:03,608
- Bollocks.
- But I can, all right!

304
00:30:03,675 --> 00:30:06,644
Murdoch: Did you everfind
those binoculars forthe lookouts?

305
00:30:06,711 --> 00:30:08,646
Haven't seen them
since Southampton.

306
00:30:08,713 --> 00:30:11,783
Well, I'll be on my rounds.
Cheerio.

307
00:30:43,114 --> 00:30:45,383
You're trembling.

308
00:30:45,450 --> 00:30:49,654
Don't worry.
I'll be all right.

309
00:31:10,308 --> 00:31:13,645
- They ran down there.
- Right.

310
00:31:22,820 --> 00:31:25,089
Lovejoy:
Anything missing?

311
00:31:49,447 --> 00:31:51,683
I've got a better idea.

312
00:32:03,361 --> 00:32:05,263
Gotcha!

313
00:32:06,764 --> 00:32:10,702
( RoseLaughing)

314
00:32:12,270 --> 00:32:14,706
( Laughing)

315
00:32:14,772 --> 00:32:17,909
Did you see those guys' faces?

316
00:32:17,976 --> 00:32:20,445
Did you see the...

317
00:32:26,184 --> 00:32:29,087
When the ship docks...

318
00:32:29,153 --> 00:32:31,089
I'm getting offwith you.

319
00:32:31,156 --> 00:32:33,424
This is crazy.

320
00:32:33,491 --> 00:32:36,461
I know.
It doesn't make any sense.

321
00:32:37,529 --> 00:32:39,464
That's why I trust it.

322
00:32:48,106 --> 00:32:51,409
( Quietly):
Oh,yes. Here, look at this.

323
00:32:51,476 --> 00:32:54,279
Oh, look at that, would you?

324
00:32:54,345 --> 00:32:57,448
- They're a bit warmerthan we are.
- Well, ifthat's what it takes

325
00:32:57,515 --> 00:33:01,186
for us to get warmer I'd rather not,
if it's all the same toyou.

326
00:33:12,297 --> 00:33:16,100
- Bugger me!
- ( Alarm Bell Clanging)

327
00:33:18,069 --> 00:33:21,206
- ( PhoneRings)
- Pick up,you bastards!

328
00:33:21,272 --> 00:33:24,142
( PhoneRinging)

329
00:33:24,209 --> 00:33:27,245
- Is there anyone there?
- Yes, what doyou see?

330
00:33:27,312 --> 00:33:31,549
- Iceberg! Right ahead!
- Thankyou.

331
00:33:31,616 --> 00:33:34,652
Iceberg! Right ahead!
Hard to starboard!

332
00:33:34,719 --> 00:33:37,055
Crewman:
Hard to starboard!

333
00:33:40,592 --> 00:33:44,929
- ( Ringing)
- Crewman: Turn, turn! Steady!

334
00:33:45,997 --> 00:33:48,967
- ( Ringing)
- ( Bell Clangs )

335
00:33:49,033 --> 00:33:51,169
Full astern!

336
00:33:53,271 --> 00:33:56,140
- Hard over.
- Helm's hard over, sir.

337
00:33:58,176 --> 00:34:01,746
- ( Ringing)
- Go, lads! Go!

338
00:34:03,748 --> 00:34:05,884
( Men Yelling OutOrders)

339
00:34:08,119 --> 00:34:12,123
Shut all the dampers!
Shut them!

340
00:34:12,190 --> 00:34:14,125
( DampersSlamming)

341
00:34:16,161 --> 00:34:18,663
Hold it.

342
00:34:18,730 --> 00:34:21,299
Hold it!

343
00:34:21,366 --> 00:34:23,268
Now, engage
the reversing engine!

344
00:34:25,770 --> 00:34:27,906
( EngineStops)

345
00:34:33,211 --> 00:34:37,182
( EngineRestarts)

346
00:34:51,396 --> 00:34:53,765
Why aren't theyturning?!

347
00:34:53,832 --> 00:34:57,802
- Is it hard over?!
- Crewman: It is,yes, sir, hard over!

348
00:35:00,972 --> 00:35:04,275
( Softly):
Come on, come on, come on.

349
00:35:04,342 --> 00:35:06,277
Turn.

350
00:35:15,587 --> 00:35:18,289
Yes.

351
00:35:22,360 --> 00:35:25,096
It's going to hit!

352
00:35:36,307 --> 00:35:38,977
Jesus Christ.

353
00:35:51,456 --> 00:35:54,325
( Glass Tinkling)

354
00:35:58,062 --> 00:36:01,132
- ( Softly):Jesus.
- Hard to port!

355
00:36:01,199 --> 00:36:03,635
Crewman:
Hard to port!

356
00:36:06,371 --> 00:36:09,340
( MenScreaming)

357
00:36:12,677 --> 00:36:15,246
Get back!

358
00:36:26,891 --> 00:36:28,827
( Screaming)

359
00:36:31,529 --> 00:36:34,032
- ( Hissing)
- ( Screams)

360
00:36:41,372 --> 00:36:44,909
- ( MetaIDoors Closing)
- Come on, let's go!

361
00:36:44,976 --> 00:36:48,446
Get out the door!
They're closing the doors! Get out!

362
00:36:48,513 --> 00:36:51,616
Get out! Get out! Get out!

363
00:36:54,786 --> 00:36:57,322
Get out the door! Go on!

364
00:36:57,388 --> 00:37:00,525
Go on! Come on, lads!
Go, lads, go!

365
00:37:07,799 --> 00:37:09,968
Get out!

366
00:37:13,104 --> 00:37:15,940
( Screams)

367
00:37:16,007 --> 00:37:18,276
( DoorsSlamming)

368
00:37:28,753 --> 00:37:32,857
( Softly): Oh, my God.
That was a close shave, weren't it?

369
00:37:32,924 --> 00:37:36,227
Smell ice, can you?
Bleeding Christ.

370
00:37:39,898 --> 00:37:43,968
Note the time
and enter it in the log.

371
00:37:48,406 --> 00:37:50,542
What was that, Mr. Murdoch?

372
00:37:50,608 --> 00:37:54,679
An iceberg, sir.
I put her hard to starboard

373
00:37:54,746 --> 00:37:57,448
and ran the engines full astern
but it was too close.

374
00:37:57,515 --> 00:38:00,385
I tried to port round it
but she hit and the...

375
00:38:00,451 --> 00:38:04,088
- Close the watertight doors.
- Murdoch: The doors are closed, sir.

376
00:38:06,524 --> 00:38:08,960
- All stop.
- Crewman: Aye, sir!

377
00:38:11,029 --> 00:38:13,164
( Ringing)

378
00:38:15,834 --> 00:38:18,303
Find the carpenter.
Get him to sound the ship.

379
00:38:18,369 --> 00:38:20,371
Yes, sir!

380
00:38:22,974 --> 00:38:25,677
Fabrizio:
Porca puttana!

381
00:38:25,743 --> 00:38:28,346
Che cazzo e?

382
00:38:29,681 --> 00:38:34,319
Come on, let's get the hell
out of here! Come on, hurry up.

383
00:38:39,123 --> 00:38:42,126
Excuse me. Why have the engines stopped?
I felt a shudder.

384
00:38:42,193 --> 00:38:44,796
I shouldn't worry, madam.
We've likelythrown a propeller blade.

385
00:38:44,863 --> 00:38:47,765
That's the shudderyou felt.
May I bringyou anything?

386
00:38:47,832 --> 00:38:49,868
No, thankyou.

387
00:38:54,906 --> 00:38:56,841
Man:
Did you see anything?

388
00:38:56,908 --> 00:38:59,344
Man:
I don't see anything now, doyou?

389
00:38:59,410 --> 00:39:01,346
( Commotion)

390
00:39:01,412 --> 00:39:04,682
Ifthis is the direction the rats
are going that's good enough for me.

391
00:39:06,451 --> 00:39:09,954
Crewman: Please, sir, please.
Everything's under control.

392
00:39:11,289 --> 00:39:13,491
- You there.
- Sir, there is no emergency.

393
00:39:13,558 --> 00:39:16,427
- Yes, there is, I have been robbed.
- Get the master-at-arms.

394
00:39:16,494 --> 00:39:19,230
- Now,you moron!
- Yes, sir.

395
00:39:19,297 --> 00:39:21,466
( Men Laughing)

396
00:39:23,301 --> 00:39:26,671
Hey,you're going to miss the fun.
Did you see what happened?

397
00:39:26,738 --> 00:39:29,941
No, I missed it.
Apparently, it hit overthere.

398
00:39:30,008 --> 00:39:32,644
Crewman: Boiler room six
is flooded eight feet above the plate.

399
00:39:32,710 --> 00:39:35,613
And the mail hold is worse. She's
all buckled in in the forward hold.

400
00:39:35,680 --> 00:39:38,016
- Can you shore up?
- Not unless the pumps get ahead.

401
00:39:38,082 --> 00:39:40,318
Haveyou seen the damage
in the mail hold?

402
00:39:40,385 --> 00:39:43,321
- No, she's already underwater.
- This is bad.

403
00:39:45,223 --> 00:39:47,325
We should tell
Mother and Cal.

404
00:39:48,393 --> 00:39:51,229
I thinkthey're very good, sir.

405
00:39:53,164 --> 00:39:56,234
Don't touch anything.
I want the entire room photographed.

406
00:39:56,301 --> 00:39:58,703
Rose:
Just keep holding my hand.

407
00:40:00,872 --> 00:40:03,308
We've been looking
foryou, miss.

408
00:40:06,511 --> 00:40:09,314
Rose ( Sighs):
Well, here we go.

409
00:40:15,353 --> 00:40:18,089
Something serious has happened.

410
00:40:18,156 --> 00:40:20,091
Yes, it has.

411
00:40:21,192 --> 00:40:24,662
Indeed. Two things dearto me
have disappeared this evening.

412
00:40:24,729 --> 00:40:28,099
Now that one is back I have a pretty
good idea where to find the other.

413
00:40:28,166 --> 00:40:30,702
- Search him.
- Takeyour coat off, sir.

414
00:40:30,768 --> 00:40:32,704
- Now what?
- Come on.

415
00:40:32,770 --> 00:40:36,541
Cal, what areyou doing? We're in the
middle ofan emergency. What's going on?

416
00:40:36,608 --> 00:40:38,743
- Is this it?
- That's it.

417
00:40:38,810 --> 00:40:41,112
This is horseshit!

418
00:40:41,179 --> 00:40:44,849
- Don'tyou believe it, Rose. Don't!
- He couldn't have.

419
00:40:44,916 --> 00:40:47,585
Ofcourse he could.
It's easy enough for a professional.

420
00:40:47,652 --> 00:40:50,355
But I was with him the whole time.
This is absurd.

421
00:40:50,421 --> 00:40:55,059
Perhaps he did it whileyou were putting
your clothes back on, dear.

422
00:40:55,126 --> 00:40:57,362
Real slick, Cal.
Rose, they put it in my pocket.

423
00:40:57,428 --> 00:41:00,532
- Shut up.
- It isn't even your pocket, is it, son?

424
00:41:00,598 --> 00:41:03,668
Property ofA. L. Ryerson.

425
00:41:06,471 --> 00:41:08,873
- That was reported stolen today.
- I just borrowed it.

426
00:41:08,940 --> 00:41:12,610
- I was going to return it.
- We have an honest thief here, do we?

427
00:41:12,677 --> 00:41:15,914
You know I didn't do this, Rose.
You know it.

428
00:41:15,980 --> 00:41:18,917
Don'tyou believe them, Rose.
You know I didn't do it.

429
00:41:18,983 --> 00:41:21,219
- Come on, let's go.
- You know I didn't do it, Rose. Rose!

430
00:41:21,286 --> 00:41:23,721
Come on, son.
There's a good lad.

431
00:41:23,788 --> 00:41:27,225
- Come on.
- You know I didn't do it! You know me!

432
00:41:29,227 --> 00:41:31,863
Ismay:
Most unfortunate, Captain.

433
00:41:34,799 --> 00:41:38,303
Water... 1 4 feet above
the keel in ten minutes--

434
00:41:38,369 --> 00:41:41,873
In the forepeak, in all three holds
and in the boiler room six.

435
00:41:41,940 --> 00:41:44,642
- That's right, sir.
- When can we get underway, damn it?

436
00:41:44,709 --> 00:41:46,744
That's five compartments.

437
00:41:48,146 --> 00:41:51,850
She can stay afloat with the first
four compartments breached

438
00:41:51,916 --> 00:41:54,486
but not five-- not five.

439
00:41:54,552 --> 00:41:57,222
As she goes down bythe head
the water

440
00:41:57,288 --> 00:42:01,593
will spill overthe tops of bulkheads
at E deckfrom one to the next.

441
00:42:01,659 --> 00:42:04,562
Back and back.
There's no stopping it.

442
00:42:04,629 --> 00:42:06,564
The pumps--
Ifwe opened the doors--

443
00:42:06,631 --> 00:42:09,534
The pumps buyyou time,
but minutes only.

444
00:42:09,601 --> 00:42:12,437
From this moment,
no matterwhat we do

445
00:42:12,504 --> 00:42:15,507
Titanicwill founder.

446
00:42:17,642 --> 00:42:19,611
But this ship can't sink.

447
00:42:19,677 --> 00:42:22,714
She's made of iron, sir.
I assureyou, she can...

448
00:42:22,780 --> 00:42:25,183
and she will.

449
00:42:25,250 --> 00:42:27,785
It is a mathematical certainty.

450
00:42:31,055 --> 00:42:33,024
How much time?

451
00:42:39,931 --> 00:42:43,034
An hour. Two at most.

452
00:42:47,839 --> 00:42:50,809
And how many aboard,
Mr. Murdoch?

453
00:42:50,875 --> 00:42:53,878
2,200 souls on board, sir.

454
00:43:00,585 --> 00:43:04,989
Well, I believeyou may get
your headlines, Mr. Ismay.

455
00:43:21,840 --> 00:43:26,177
Oh, it is a little slut, isn't it? Will
you look at me when I'm talking toyou.

456
00:43:26,244 --> 00:43:28,179
( KnockAtDoor)

457
00:43:28,246 --> 00:43:30,181
- Mr. Hockley?
- Not now, we're busy.

458
00:43:30,248 --> 00:43:33,485
Sir, I've been told to askyou to please
put on your lifebelts and come up to--

459
00:43:33,585 --> 00:43:35,553
I said not now.

460
00:43:35,620 --> 00:43:38,656
I'm sorryto inconvenienceyou,
Mr. Hockley, but it's Captain's orders.

461
00:43:38,756 --> 00:43:42,260
Now, please, dress warmly.
It's quite cold out tonight.

462
00:43:42,360 --> 00:43:45,563
Now, may I suggest
topcoats and hats.

463
00:43:45,663 --> 00:43:49,801
- This is ridiculous.
- Not to worry, miss.

464
00:43:49,901 --> 00:43:51,903
I am sure
it'sjust a precaution.

465
00:43:52,003 --> 00:43:54,205
Everybody up!
Lifebelts on!

466
00:43:54,305 --> 00:43:57,342
- ( MenScreaming Orders)
- What's heyelling about?

467
00:43:57,442 --> 00:43:59,377
Everybody up!
Putyour lifebelts on!

468
00:43:59,444 --> 00:44:01,679
- What's the ruckus?
-Just putyour lifebelts on!

469
00:44:01,779 --> 00:44:04,182
Crewman:
C.QD.?

470
00:44:04,249 --> 00:44:06,184
Sir?

471
00:44:07,785 --> 00:44:10,221
That's right-- C.QD.
The distress call.

472
00:44:10,288 --> 00:44:12,223
That's our position.

473
00:44:14,592 --> 00:44:16,528
( Sighs)

474
00:44:16,594 --> 00:44:19,564
Tell whoever responds
that we're going down bythe head.

475
00:44:19,664 --> 00:44:22,634
We need immediate assistance.

476
00:44:30,809 --> 00:44:33,178
Blimey.

477
00:44:42,253 --> 00:44:46,624
Keep lowering!
Keep lowering!

478
00:44:51,563 --> 00:44:54,532
( Crewman Yelling OutOrders)

479
00:45:06,044 --> 00:45:09,180
Mr. Wilde! Mr. Wilde,
where are the passengers?

480
00:45:09,280 --> 00:45:12,717
We moved them back inside.
It's too damn cold and noisyforthem.

481
00:45:12,784 --> 00:45:15,220
You there!
(Blows Whistle)

482
00:45:15,286 --> 00:45:17,455
Get down here and
help with these lines.

483
00:45:17,555 --> 00:45:21,493
( Orchestra Playing
"Alexander's RagtimeBand")

484
00:45:24,062 --> 00:45:26,564
( People Conversing)

