- Crewman: Please putyour lifebelts on.
- Hey, sonny, what's doing?

487
00:45:38,276 --> 00:45:41,246
You got us all trussed up here
and now we're cooling our heels.

488
00:45:41,312 --> 00:45:43,381
Sorry, ma'am.
Let me go and find out.

489
00:45:43,481 --> 00:45:47,318
I don't think anybody knows
what the hell's going on around here.

490
00:45:47,385 --> 00:45:50,455
It's the goddamned English
doing everything bythe book.

491
00:45:50,555 --> 00:45:52,957
There's no need for language,
Mr. Hockley.

492
00:45:53,024 --> 00:45:55,226
Go back and turn
the heaters on in our rooms.

493
00:45:55,326 --> 00:45:57,295
I'd like a cup oftea
when I return.

494
00:45:57,362 --> 00:45:59,330
Yes, ma'am.

495
00:46:08,406 --> 00:46:10,475
Mr. Andrews.

496
00:46:11,609 --> 00:46:15,513
I saw the iceberg
and I see it in your eyes.

497
00:46:15,580 --> 00:46:18,049
Please tell me the truth.

498
00:46:25,323 --> 00:46:28,493
The ship will sink.

499
00:46:28,593 --> 00:46:32,564
- You're certain.
- Yes, in an hour or so....

500
00:46:32,664 --> 00:46:36,267
all this will be
at the bottom ofthe Atlantic.

501
00:46:36,367 --> 00:46:40,271
- What?
- Please, tell onlywhoyou must?

502
00:46:40,338 --> 00:46:42,807
I don't want to
be responsible for a panic

503
00:46:42,907 --> 00:46:45,877
and get to a boat quickly,
don't wait.

504
00:46:45,977 --> 00:46:48,813
You rememberwhat I told you
about the boats?

505
00:46:51,950 --> 00:46:53,885
Yes.

506
00:46:55,086 --> 00:46:57,622
I understand.

507
00:47:04,629 --> 00:47:07,031
Over here, sir.

508
00:47:07,098 --> 00:47:09,667
Sir, they need you
up in the second-class purser's office.

509
00:47:09,767 --> 00:47:12,303
- There's a big mob up there.
- Go on, I'll keep an eye on him.

510
00:47:12,403 --> 00:47:15,273
Aye, right.

511
00:47:28,386 --> 00:47:32,190
Sir! Carpathia says
they're making 1 7 knots.

512
00:47:32,257 --> 00:47:35,393
Full steam forthem, sir.

513
00:47:35,493 --> 00:47:37,428
She's the only one responding?

514
00:47:37,495 --> 00:47:40,765
The only one close, sir.
She says they can be here in four hours.

515
00:47:40,865 --> 00:47:43,234
Four hours?

516
00:47:48,006 --> 00:47:49,941
Thankyou, Bride.

517
00:47:53,812 --> 00:47:55,780
( Softly):
My God.

518
00:47:55,847 --> 00:47:59,417
( Crewmen Yelling OutOrders)

519
00:48:03,955 --> 00:48:07,358
Sir! We are swung out
and ready, sir.

520
00:48:08,493 --> 00:48:13,031
Hadn't we better get the women
and children into the boat, sir?

521
00:48:14,299 --> 00:48:17,168
- Yes, we do.
- Sir?

522
00:48:19,737 --> 00:48:23,942
Women and children first. Yes.

523
00:48:24,042 --> 00:48:25,977
Yes, sir.

524
00:48:27,812 --> 00:48:31,382
Crewman ( Yelling): Ladies
and gentlemen,your attention please!

525
00:48:31,483 --> 00:48:34,219
Step this way, please.
That's right.

526
00:48:34,319 --> 00:48:36,454
Come towards me.

527
00:48:36,554 --> 00:48:39,491
Thankyou. Good.

528
00:48:39,557 --> 00:48:43,995
Forthe time being, I shall require
onlywomen and children.

529
00:48:44,095 --> 00:48:46,431
Man:
Right here.

530
00:48:46,498 --> 00:48:48,466
All right, boys,
like the captain said

531
00:48:48,533 --> 00:48:50,869
nice and cheery
so there's no panic.

532
00:48:50,935 --> 00:48:52,871
"Wedding Dance."

533
00:48:52,937 --> 00:48:55,206
( Orchestra BeginsPlaying)

534
00:49:00,778 --> 00:49:03,748
Lifebelts on!
Here, putyour lifebelts on.

535
00:49:03,815 --> 00:49:07,185
Putyour lifebelts on.
Here, putyour lifebelt on.

536
00:49:07,252 --> 00:49:09,721
Here, come on, here.

537
00:49:11,723 --> 00:49:14,692
( Commotion)

538
00:49:14,759 --> 00:49:17,662
Crewman: It isn't time
to go up to the boatsyet.

539
00:49:17,729 --> 00:49:19,697
Please stay calm.

540
00:49:19,798 --> 00:49:22,801
Look, please, make sure, everybody,
you've gotyour lifebelts on

541
00:49:22,901 --> 00:49:25,904
and gentlemen, allow the women
and children through to the front.

542
00:49:26,004 --> 00:49:29,374
- What are we doing, Mommy?
- We'rejust waiting, dear.

543
00:49:29,440 --> 00:49:31,843
When they're finished putting
the first-class people in the boats...

544
00:49:31,910 --> 00:49:35,079
they'll start with us and
we'll want to be all ready, won't we?

545
00:49:35,180 --> 00:49:37,348
( MenArguing)

546
00:49:37,448 --> 00:49:39,517
Go and get some help.

547
00:49:39,617 --> 00:49:42,821
Lower away!
Left and right together!

548
00:49:42,921 --> 00:49:46,491
Steady! Both sides together.

549
00:49:46,591 --> 00:49:49,060
Steady! Steady!

550
00:49:49,127 --> 00:49:51,229
Steady!

551
00:49:51,329 --> 00:49:53,398
Stop! Stop!

552
00:49:53,498 --> 00:49:57,669
- ( Screaming)
- Hold the left side! Right side only!

553
00:49:57,769 --> 00:50:00,605
Right side only!
Right side only!

554
00:50:00,672 --> 00:50:03,174
Hold the left side!
Right side down!

555
00:50:03,274 --> 00:50:05,510
Lower awaytogether!

556
00:50:06,611 --> 00:50:08,546
Steady, lads!

557
00:50:11,850 --> 00:50:13,852
( Explosion)

558
00:50:13,952 --> 00:50:16,988
( Passengers Gasp )

559
00:50:55,760 --> 00:50:59,964
You know, I do believe
this ship may sink.

560
00:51:00,064 --> 00:51:03,001
I've been asked to giveyou

561
00:51:03,067 --> 00:51:05,970
this small token
ofour appreciation.

562
00:51:08,439 --> 00:51:11,309
Compliments of
Mr. Caledon Hockley.

563
00:51:17,448 --> 00:51:20,885
Come on, sister,you heard
the man-- into the boat.

564
00:51:20,952 --> 00:51:23,054
Any room for a gentleman,
gentlemen?

565
00:51:23,154 --> 00:51:26,357
Crewman:
Onlywomen at this time, sir.

566
00:51:26,457 --> 00:51:30,695
Will the lifeboats be seated
according to class?

567
00:51:32,163 --> 00:51:35,066
I hope they're
not too crowded.

568
00:51:35,133 --> 00:51:37,602
Oh, Mother, shut up!

569
00:51:37,669 --> 00:51:41,973
Don'tyou understand? The water is
freezing and there aren't enough boats.

570
00:51:42,073 --> 00:51:47,111
Not enough by half. Halfthe people
on this ship are going to die.

571
00:51:47,212 --> 00:51:49,147
Not the better half.

572
00:51:50,949 --> 00:51:54,919
Come on, Ruth, get in the boat.
First-class seats are right up here.

573
00:51:55,019 --> 00:51:57,355
You know, it's a pity
I didn't keep that drawing.

574
00:51:57,422 --> 00:52:00,358
It'll be worth
a lot more by morning.

575
00:52:02,894 --> 00:52:06,397
You unimaginable bastard.

576
00:52:06,498 --> 00:52:10,935
Molly: Come on, Rose, darling.
There's plenty of room foryou.

577
00:52:11,002 --> 00:52:13,171
Come on, Rose.
You're next, darling.

578
00:52:13,271 --> 00:52:15,206
Come into the boat, Rose.

579
00:52:17,709 --> 00:52:22,480
- Come.
- Rose, get into the boat.

580
00:52:22,580 --> 00:52:24,949
Rose.

581
00:52:25,016 --> 00:52:26,985
Good-bye, Mother.

582
00:52:28,820 --> 00:52:31,556
Rose! Rose, come back here!

583
00:52:31,656 --> 00:52:34,759
Where areyou going?
To him?

584
00:52:34,859 --> 00:52:37,595
To be a whore to a gutter rat?

585
00:52:37,695 --> 00:52:40,365
I'd rather be his whore
than yourwife.

586
00:52:43,168 --> 00:52:45,370
No. No!

587
00:52:45,470 --> 00:52:48,540
- I said no!
- ( Hawking)

588
00:52:48,640 --> 00:52:50,642
Ruth:
Rose! Please stop!

589
00:52:50,742 --> 00:52:52,777
Crewman:
And lower away!

590
00:52:52,877 --> 00:52:54,846
- Rose!
- Man the tiller!

591
00:52:54,913 --> 00:52:57,148
- No, wait!
- Lower away!

592
00:52:57,248 --> 00:52:59,617
- Rose!
- Lowertogether!

593
00:53:04,656 --> 00:53:06,925
Help!

594
00:53:07,025 --> 00:53:09,160
Can anybody hear me?

595
00:53:09,260 --> 00:53:12,230
( BangingPipe)
Hello, help me!

596
00:53:12,330 --> 00:53:15,500
( Distantly):
Help me!

597
00:53:15,600 --> 00:53:18,169
Can anybody hear me?

598
00:53:18,269 --> 00:53:22,273
Somebody help me, please!

599
00:53:22,373 --> 00:53:24,576
Rose:
Mr. Andrews?

600
00:53:27,078 --> 00:53:29,981
- Steward, checkthe starboard corridor.
- Yes, Mr. Andrews.

601
00:53:30,048 --> 00:53:32,550
Madam, please put on a lifebelt.
Get to the boat deck immediately.

602
00:53:32,650 --> 00:53:34,819
Lucy, for God's sake,
put on your lifebelt.

603
00:53:34,919 --> 00:53:37,055
- Set a good example.
- Yes, sir.

604
00:53:37,155 --> 00:53:40,592
- Anyone in here?
- Mr. Andrews? Mr. Andrews, thank God.

605
00:53:40,658 --> 00:53:42,894
Where would the master-at-arms
take someone under arrest?

606
00:53:42,994 --> 00:53:45,697
What? You have to get
to a boat right away.

607
00:53:45,797 --> 00:53:50,235
No! I'm doing this with orwithoutyour
help, sir, but without will take longer.

608
00:53:52,904 --> 00:53:56,741
Take the elevatorto the bottom. Go
to the left down the crewman's passage.

609
00:53:56,808 --> 00:54:01,045
Then go right and left again at the
stairs. You'll come to a long corridor.

610
00:54:05,950 --> 00:54:08,453
- This could be bad.
- (WaterGurgling)

611
00:54:11,189 --> 00:54:14,492
Oh, shit. Oh, shit!

612
00:54:15,760 --> 00:54:19,164
( Struggling)

613
00:54:19,230 --> 00:54:22,433
- Excuse me, thankyou.
- Crewman: The lifts are closed.

614
00:54:22,534 --> 00:54:25,236
- Woman: I do not care...
- The lifts are--

615
00:54:25,336 --> 00:54:28,773
I'm sorry, miss,
but the lifts are closed.

616
00:54:28,840 --> 00:54:33,578
I'm through being polite, goddamn it!
Now take me down!

617
00:54:33,678 --> 00:54:35,613
E deck.

618
00:54:39,384 --> 00:54:41,886
Come on. Oh, come on.

619
00:54:44,422 --> 00:54:46,391
( Yells)

620
00:54:57,202 --> 00:54:59,270
( Screams)

621
00:54:59,370 --> 00:55:02,040
- I'm going back up!
- No!

622
00:55:02,140 --> 00:55:04,342
No, no!

623
00:55:07,412 --> 00:55:09,380
Come back!
I'm going back up.

624
00:55:09,481 --> 00:55:11,749
I'm going back up!

625
00:55:19,591 --> 00:55:22,260
Crew passage.

626
00:55:22,360 --> 00:55:24,462
Crew passage.

627
00:55:34,205 --> 00:55:37,642
( BreathingHard)

628
00:55:44,149 --> 00:55:45,650
Jack?

629
00:55:49,053 --> 00:55:50,755
Jack?

630
00:55:54,626 --> 00:55:56,895
Jack?!

631
00:55:56,995 --> 00:55:58,963
-Jack?
- Rose!

632
00:55:59,030 --> 00:56:01,199
Jack?!

633
00:56:01,299 --> 00:56:03,835
Rose, I'm in here!
I'm in here.

634
00:56:03,935 --> 00:56:06,404
-Jack?!
- I'm in here.

635
00:56:06,471 --> 00:56:08,406
-Jack?!
- Rose!

636
00:56:08,473 --> 00:56:10,675
Jack!Jack! I'm sorry.

637
00:56:10,775 --> 00:56:13,144
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

638
00:56:14,212 --> 00:56:17,882
- That guy Lovejoy put it in my pocket.
- I know, I know, I know, I know.

639
00:56:17,982 --> 00:56:21,219
Listen, Rose,you're going to have
to find a spare key, all right?

640
00:56:21,319 --> 00:56:23,988
Look in that cabinet
right there.

641
00:56:24,088 --> 00:56:26,624
It's a little
silver one, Rose.

642
00:56:26,724 --> 00:56:28,660
Silver.

643
00:56:28,726 --> 00:56:32,664
- These are all brass ones!
- Check right here, Rose.

644
00:56:36,701 --> 00:56:38,703
Rose...

645
00:56:38,803 --> 00:56:40,939
how did you find out
I didn't do it?

646
00:56:41,039 --> 00:56:43,007
I didn't.

647
00:56:43,074 --> 00:56:46,044
I just realized I already knew.

648
00:56:47,111 --> 00:56:49,714
- Keep looking.
- Oh.

649
00:56:56,554 --> 00:56:59,991
No key. There's no key!

650
00:57:00,058 --> 00:57:03,595
All right, Rose, listen. You're going
to have to go find some help.

651
00:57:03,695 --> 00:57:05,797
It'll be all right.

652
00:57:10,201 --> 00:57:12,137
I'll be right back.

653
00:57:19,377 --> 00:57:21,913
I'lljust wait here.

654
00:57:33,691 --> 00:57:35,827
Hello, is there anyone here?

655
00:57:37,028 --> 00:57:40,465
Hello? ls there anybody
down here?

656
00:57:41,800 --> 00:57:43,768
We need help! Hello!

657
00:57:43,868 --> 00:57:45,603
Damn it.

658
00:57:51,876 --> 00:57:56,281
Can anybody hear me?
Please, hello! Hello!

659
00:57:57,749 --> 00:58:01,119
Oh, thank God.
Wait, please, I need your help.

660
00:58:01,186 --> 00:58:03,655
There's a man back here and--
Wait!

661
00:58:08,026 --> 00:58:10,328
Hello?

662
00:58:20,772 --> 00:58:23,975
( LoudRumbling)

663
00:58:24,075 --> 00:58:27,312
( RoseBreathingHard)

664
00:58:35,286 --> 00:58:38,490
- Hello?
- Ah, miss,you shouldn't be here now.

665
00:58:38,590 --> 00:58:41,192
- Please, I need your help.
- This way, quickly.

666
00:58:41,292 --> 00:58:44,329
There is a man down here
and he is trapped. Please.

667
00:58:44,429 --> 00:58:46,498
- There's no need to panic.
- No, I'm not panicking.

668
00:58:46,598 --> 00:58:48,800
You're going the wrong way!

669
00:58:48,900 --> 00:58:51,136
Let go of me, listen!

670
00:58:55,874 --> 00:58:59,577
- To hell with you.
- Oh!

671
00:58:59,677 --> 00:59:02,147
( Ship Creaking)

672
00:59:34,979 --> 00:59:36,948
( Softly):
Oh, my God...

673
00:59:41,653 --> 00:59:44,289
- ( Explosion)
- ( Crackling)

674
00:59:55,400 --> 00:59:57,602
( Gasping)

675
01:00:15,487 --> 01:00:18,923
( LoudRumbling)

676
01:00:25,130 --> 01:00:28,533
-Jack!
- Rose!

677
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:32,670
- Will this work?
- I guess we'll find out.

678
01:00:32,770 --> 01:00:34,739
Come on.

679
01:00:36,774 --> 01:00:40,712
Wait, wait, wait, wait. Try a couple
of practice swings overthere.

680
01:00:40,778 --> 01:00:43,348
All right.

681
01:00:45,950 --> 01:00:49,654
Good, now tryto hit
the same mark again, Rose.

682
01:00:49,754 --> 01:00:51,723
You can do it.

683
01:00:56,427 --> 01:00:58,830
Okay, that's enough practice.

684
01:00:58,897 --> 01:01:01,866
Come on, Rose,
you can do it. Listen.

685
01:01:01,966 --> 01:01:04,836
Just hit it really hard
and reallyfast.

686
01:01:06,271 --> 01:01:09,507
Wait, open your hands up
a little more.

687
01:01:09,607 --> 01:01:11,743
- Like that?
- Right.

688
01:01:11,843 --> 01:01:14,579
Listen, Rose, I trustyou.

689
01:01:18,983 --> 01:01:20,919
Go!

690
01:01:20,985 --> 01:01:23,455
-( Clang)
-( Gasps)

691
01:01:23,521 --> 01:01:26,157
( ScreamingAndLaughing)

692
01:01:26,257 --> 01:01:29,561
You did it!
Come on, let's go.

693
01:01:29,661 --> 01:01:32,330
Oh, shit, this is cold.
Oh, shit!

694
01:01:32,430 --> 01:01:34,132
Shit, shit.

695
01:01:40,805 --> 01:01:44,742
- This is the way out.
- We have to find anotherway. Come on.

696
01:01:44,809 --> 01:01:47,612
- Tiller: Pull.
- (Orchestra Playing)

697
01:01:47,712 --> 01:01:51,649
Pull!
Putyour backs into it, pull!

698
01:01:51,716 --> 01:01:55,520
( DistantShouting)

699
01:01:55,620 --> 01:01:57,555
Pull!

700
01:01:57,622 --> 01:02:00,558
Now, there's something
you don't see every day.

701
01:02:00,625 --> 01:02:03,061
Pull!

702
01:02:06,498 --> 01:02:08,867
( DistantExplosion)

703
01:02:10,735 --> 01:02:13,538
( Shouting)

704
01:02:22,881 --> 01:02:25,183
Crewman:
What's this luggage doing here?

705
01:02:25,283 --> 01:02:30,221
- Get rid of it, we need the room.
- (Crewman Giving Orders)

706
01:02:30,288 --> 01:02:32,257
( Crying)

707
01:02:32,323 --> 01:02:34,259
Keep calm.

708
01:02:34,325 --> 01:02:36,427
No!

709
01:02:40,732 --> 01:02:44,002
-Lovejoy.
-She's not on the starboard side either.

710
01:02:44,102 --> 01:02:46,638
We're running out oftime
and this strutting martinet

711
01:02:46,738 --> 01:02:48,673
isn't letting
any men on at all.

712
01:02:48,740 --> 01:02:51,309
There's one on the other side
letting men on.

713
01:02:51,409 --> 01:02:56,080
Well, then, that's our play. We'll need
some insurance first. Come on.

714
01:02:56,181 --> 01:02:58,183
- ( Pounding)
- This way.

715
01:02:58,283 --> 01:03:01,853
- All the way down here.
- (Jack Yelling)

716
01:03:01,953 --> 01:03:06,224
Steward:
Here! What doyou thinkyou're doing?

717
01:03:06,324 --> 01:03:09,727
You'll have to payforthat,you know.
That's White Star Line property.

718
01:03:09,794 --> 01:03:12,664
Both:
Shut up!

719
01:03:12,730 --> 01:03:16,901
Will you hold the boat a moment?
I just have to run backto my room--

720
01:03:17,001 --> 01:03:20,538
Sit down! She's the last.
All right to lower.

721
01:03:20,638 --> 01:03:23,708
Mr. Lightoller, why are the boats
being launched halffull?

722
01:03:23,808 --> 01:03:26,878
- Not now, Mr. Andrews.
- There, look, 20 or so

723
01:03:26,978 --> 01:03:30,648
in a boat built for 65,
and I saw one boat with only 1 2-- 1 2!

724
01:03:30,748 --> 01:03:35,053
Well, we weren't sure ofthe weight,
Mr. Andrews. These boats may buckle.

725
01:03:35,153 --> 01:03:39,557
Rubbish! Theywere tested in Belfast
with the weight of70 men!

726
01:03:39,624 --> 01:03:43,128
Now, fill these boats,
Mr. Lightoller, for God's sake, man!

727
01:03:49,200 --> 01:03:52,403
Please, I need more women
and children, please.

728
01:03:56,441 --> 01:03:59,410
Crewman: Get back in there.
This is not an exit.

729
01:03:59,511 --> 01:04:02,113
Get back in there.
This is not an exit.

730
01:04:04,249 --> 01:04:07,952
You can't keep us locked in here like
animals. The ship's bloody sinking!

731
01:04:08,052 --> 01:04:11,589
Bring forward the women!
Unlockthe gates.

